00:26:44,900 --> 00:26:45,000
Now,

703
00:26:45,000 --> 00:26:46,940
what's the curl of the electric field equal to?

704
00:26:48,620 --> 00:26:51,520
The time derivative of the magnetic field.

705
00:26:56,120 --> 00:26:59,420
This says that a changing magnetic field,

706
00:26:59,540 --> 00:27:01,640
if the magnetic field in space changes,

707
00:27:01,940 --> 00:27:04,760
it necessarily creates an electric field.

708
00:27:06,020 --> 00:27:08,120
If B dot is not zero,

709
00:27:08,260 --> 00:27:08,740
in other words,

710
00:27:08,740 --> 00:27:10,840
if a magnetic field is changing with time,

711
00:27:11,420 --> 00:27:13,120
it creates an electric field.

712
00:27:13,180 --> 00:27:13,820
For example,

713
00:27:15,919 --> 00:27:17,760
supposing we started,

714
00:27:17,940 --> 00:27:19,300
let's take a solenoid,

715
00:27:19,380 --> 00:27:21,840
but let's make it infinitely long in both directions.

