1442
00:52:50,860 --> 00:52:52,340
Because this term is symmetric

1443
00:52:52,340 --> 00:52:53,960
when I interchange mu and nu.

1444
00:52:54,280 --> 00:52:55,640
And so when I subtract

1445
00:52:56,280 --> 00:52:58,740
the same object with the opposite

1446
00:52:58,740 --> 00:53:00,200
ordering of mu and nu,

1447
00:53:00,240 --> 00:53:02,740
or the opposite dependence on mu and nu,

1448
00:53:02,880 --> 00:53:04,280
this term will cancel.

1449
00:53:04,520 --> 00:53:06,900
And the result is that this object,

1450
00:53:08,240 --> 00:53:09,940
D mu A nu,

1451
00:53:10,820 --> 00:53:12,720
which is called F mu nu,

1452
00:53:14,800 --> 00:53:16,140
that's gauge invariant.

1453
00:53:16,140 --> 00:53:17,080
It will not change

1454
00:53:17,080 --> 00:53:18,480
when you do a gauge transformation.

1455
00:53:23,640 --> 00:53:26,380
How many such objects are there?

1456
00:53:26,420 --> 00:53:27,800
How many components does it have?

1457
00:53:28,300 --> 00:53:28,820
Well,

1458
00:53:28,820 --> 00:53:29,740
offhand,

1459
00:53:29,740 --> 00:53:30,800
mu and nu

1460
00:53:30,800 --> 00:53:32,420
can run from one to four.

1461
00:53:32,720 --> 00:53:35,740
So it looks like there's 16 independent components

1462
00:53:35,740 --> 00:53:36,700
